The paper deals with computational problems related to graph homomorphisms, which are typically studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of switching operations and edge-colouring also suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.CC). Finally, the dichotomy theorem mentioned in the abstract suggests a possible connection to computational complexity theory (cs.GT).
